com.esplibrary.constants

Class PacketId

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.esplibrary.constants.PacketId

  • public class PacketId
extends java.lang.Object
    Packet ID constants class that contains all of the Packet ID's declared in the ESP specification Rev. 3.

    • Method Detail

      • getNameForPacketIdentifier

        public static java.lang.String getNameForPacketIdentifier(int packetId)
        Retrieves the String representation of the packetId value.
        Parameters:
        packetId - The packetId of the desired packet type String you want returned. Possible Values: { REQVERSION, RESPVERSION, REQSERIALNUMBER, RESPSERIALNUMBER, REQUSERBYTES, RESPUSERBYTES, REQWRITEUSERBYTES, REQFACTORYDEFAULT, REQWRITESWEEPDEFINITION, REQALLSWEEPDEFINITIONS, RESPSWEEPDEFINITION, REQDEFAULTSWEEPS, REQMAXSWEEPINDEX, RESPMAXSWEEPINDEX, RESPSWEEPWRITERESULT, REQSWEEPSECTIONS, RESPSWEEPSECTIONS, INFDISPLAYDATA, REQTURNOFFMAINDISPLAY, REQTURNONMAINDISPLAY, REQMUTEON, REQMUTEOFF, REQCHANGEMODE, REQSTARTALERTDATA, REQSTOPALERTDATA, RESPALERTDATA, RESPDATARECEIVED, REQBATTERYVOLTAGE, RESPBATTERYVOLTAGE, RESPUNSUPPORTEDPACKET, RESPREQUESTNOTPROCESSED, INFV1BUSY, RESPDATAERROR, REQSAVVYSTATUS, RESPSAVVYSTATUS, REQVEHICLESPEED, RESPVEHICLESPEED, REQOVERRIDETHUMBWHEEL, REQSETSAVVYUNMUTEENABLE, UNKNOWNPACKETTYPE } return A String representation for the supplied packetId.
